## Repair

Keeps filenames, lists, and deploy manifest in sync after manual edits.

```bash
aifabrix repair {{appName}}
```

Useful flags: `--dry-run`, `--auth <method>`, `--rbac`, `--expose`, `--sync`, `--test`.

## Validate and test

| Command | Network | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `aifabrix validate {{appName}}` | Off | Schemas and files only |
| `aifabrix test {{appName}}` | Off | Local checks |
| `aifabrix test-integration {{appName}}` | On | Needs login + dataplane |
| `aifabrix test-e2e {{appName}}` | On | E2E for every datasource; uploads local files first unless `--no-sync` |
| `aifabrix test-trust {{appName}}` | On | Semantic agent metadata trust (not live API E2E); uploads first unless `--no-sync` |

System-level tests publish local integration files before the run (same path as `upload`). Use **`--no-sync`** to validate against config already on the dataplane.

```bash
aifabrix test-trust {{appName}}
aifabrix test-trust {{appName}} --no-sync
aifabrix test-e2e {{appName}} --no-sync
```

Single datasource E2E:

{{#if hasDatasources}}
```bash
{{#each datasources}}
# {{displayName}}
aifabrix datasource test-e2e {{datasourceKey}} --app {{../appName}}

{{/each}}
```
{{else}}
```bash
aifabrix datasource test-e2e <datasource-key> --app {{appName}}
```
{{/if}}

Common flags: `-v` / `--verbose`, `-d` / `--debug`, `--no-async` (datasource E2E only), `--no-sync` (skip pre-run upload on system `test-e2e` / `test-trust`).

Datasource trust (one key; uploads before run unless `--no-sync`):

```bash
aifabrix datasource test-trust {{#if hasDatasources}}{{datasources.[0].datasourceKey}}{{else}}<datasource-key>{{/if}} --app {{appName}}
aifabrix datasource test-trust {{#if hasDatasources}}{{datasources.[0].datasourceKey}}{{else}}<datasource-key>{{/if}} --app {{appName}} --no-sync --revalidate
```

